Plant_Inventory.Description: Lance-leaved plant is sun-loving, drought-tolerant and highly attractive to hungry butterflies. Plant coreopsis in a sunny spot that receives at least 6 to 8 hours of direct sun a day. Coreopsis prefers a rich, well-drained soil, but will be fine in poorer, drier conditions. It has medium water needs.

Baston ni San Jose is an erect, smooth shrub which grows from 1 to 3 meters high from tuberous roots. Stems are simple or somewhat branched, and marked with leaf-scars. Leaves are mostly near the apex of the stem, and usually tinged with red or purple. It is considered antiseptic, aphrodisiac, depurative, diuretic, among many others.

Pacova is a classic, and practically no-fail houseplant because it\'s so easy to grow. Grow pacova just about anywhere. As houseplants they\'re that easy to keep!. The plants grow best in medium or bright-light spots, but tolerate low light exceedingly well. Water philodendrons enough when the soil surface dries.
